    "name": "Mesh Independence Study — Impeller Region Refinement",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the impeller and volute regions of the centrifugal pump geometry, progressing through three refinement levels (coarse: 1.2M cells, medium: 3.8M cells, fine: 9.4M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for shear-stress-derived hemolysis index at the five nominal operating points. The study targeted GCI < 5% at the medium refinement level to justify production-run mesh selection.",
